    "ocr_text": "59
March 9, 1909
Mr. Max Morris, Vice-President,
American Federation of Labor,
315 Amapel Bldg., Denver, Colo.
Dear Sir and Brother:
Enclosed you will please find copy of letter received today from the Local Union #54 of Cement Workers of Denver, Colorado, in which, as you will note, protest is made against the Denver Trades and Labor Assembly recognizing and seating delegates from an organization of Team Owners. Can you give me any information in regard to the enclosed letter and can you advise me what has been, or will be done in the matter?
Fraternally yours,
Samclompers
President
American Federation of Labor.
Enclosure:
",
